The fourth element in Row 15 of Pascal's triangle is $\binom{15}{3}$. We know that $\binom{n}{k}=\frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!}$, so $\binom{15}{3}=\frac{15!}{3!12!}$. We can simplify $\frac{15!}{12!}$ as follows: \begin{align*}
\frac{15!}{12!}&=\frac{15\times 14\times 13\times 12!}{12!}\\
&=15\times 14\times 13\\
&=\boxed{2730}.
\end{align*}

